==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skiff
<hw>Skiff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>esquif</ets>,
fr. OHG. <ets>skif</ets>, G. <ets>schiff</ets>. See
<er>Ship</er>.]</ety> <def>A small, light boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pilot of some small night-foundered <qex>skiff</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Skiff caterpillar</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
larva of a moth (<spn>Limacodes scapha</spn>); -- so called from its
peculiar shape.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skiff</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skiff
<hw>Skiff</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Skiffed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Skiffing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To navigate in a skiff.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
